These are Puzzles for 2x4 Level 6

.:: Puzzle 2x4-Level-6-1::.
There are 4 different favourite beverages: juice, lemonade, mirinda, water
There are 4 different favourite colors: blue, coral, mauve, black
1. the person who likes blue is somewhere to the left of the person who likes mauve##5
2. the person drinking lemonade is not the person who likes blue##6
3. the person who likes blue is on the right of the person who likes black##1
4. the person drinking mirinda is on the right of the person who likes mauve##1
5. the person drinking juice is on the right of the person who likes blue##1
6. the person who likes blue is not the person drinking mirinda##6

.:: Answer ::.
|            |     1      |    2     |    3     |    4    |
| Beverage   | lemonade   | water    | juice    | mirinda |
| Sport      | black | blue | mauve | coral |

 #################################

 
.:: Puzzle 2x4-Level-6-2::.
There are 4 different favourite beverages: iced-tea, milk, mirinda, sprite
4 different games are played: snooker, bridge, scrabble, domino
1. the person playing snooker is on the far right##1
2. the person drinking milk is somewhere to the left of the person drinking mirinda##5
3. the person playing domino is somewhere to the left of the person drinking sprite##5
4. the person drinking milk is not the person playing bridge##6
5. the person playing domino is on the left of the person drinking mirinda##1
6. the person playing snooker is on the right of the person playing scrabble##1
7. the person drinking sprite is on the right of the person drinking iced-tea##1
8. the person drinking mirinda is somewhere to the left of the person drinking iced-tea##5

.:: Answer ::.
|            |   1   |     2      |    3     |     4     |
| Beverage   | milk  | mirinda    | iced-tea | sprite    |
| Food       | domino | bridge | scrabble  | snooker |

 #################################

 
.:: Puzzle 2x4-Level-6-3::.
There are 4 different nationalities: pakistani, dutch, french, spanish
The people have 4 different jobs:  coach, doctor, electrician, police-officer
1. the spanish is not the coach##6
2. the doctor is not the french##6
3. the electrician is on the left or right of the dutch##3
4. the doctor is the pakistani##1
5. the dutch is on the left of the doctor##1
6. the pakistani is in an odd position##4
7. the coach is on the far left or far right##3
8. the electrician is somewhere to the left of the police-officer##5

.:: Answer ::.
|            |      1      |       2        |   3    |   4    |
| Beverage   | spanish       | dutch  | pakistani  | french |
| Job        | electrician | police-officer | doctor | coach  |

